<h2>Common Accessibility Issues That Hurt Your SEO</h2><br>

<p>Many Western Sydney businesses unknowingly use features that harm both accessibility and search rankings:</p>

<h3>1. Poor Colour Contrast</h3><br>

<p>Text that's difficult to read due to poor contrast affects users with vision impairments and increases bounce rates—a negative SEO signal. WCAG requires a contrast ratio of at least 4.5:1 for normal text.</p>

<h3>2. Missing Form Labels</h3><br>

<p>Unlabelled form fields create barriers for screen reader users and make it harder for Google to understand your conversion funnels.</p>

<h3>3. Inaccessible Navigation Menus</h3><br>

<p>Dropdown menus that only work with mouse hover exclude keyboard users and often use JavaScript that search engines struggle to crawl.</p>

<h3>4. Auto-Playing Media</h3><br>

<p>Videos that auto-play with sound create barriers for users with cognitive disabilities and negatively impact Core Web Vitals scores.</p>

<h3>5. Generic Link Text</h3><br>

<p>Links labelled "click here" or "read more" provide no context for screen reader users and waste valuable SEO anchor text opportunities.</p>

